summary: This appears to be an email header or file path reference related to the US v. Epstein case, specifically concerning the organization of materials for witnesses and cooperators. It indicates administrative handling of case-related communications.

locations.description: A shared network drive path at the US Department of Justice, likely used for storing case materials related to the US v. Epstein proceedings.

keyFacts: The document is an email header dated December 16, 2019, referencing the US v. Epstein case (docket 2018R0161).
It references a shared DOJ network drive path used for storing materials related to 'Witnesses & Cooperators Emails'.
The file is labeled EFTA00016396, indicating it is part of a larger document set or evidence tracking system.
The subject matter pertains to the administrative organization of communications involving witnesses and cooperators in the Epstein case.
